Russia Will Play the Czech Republic in Final of Women's Tennis’s Fed Cup

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-04-17T19:21:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/russia-czech-republic-will-meet-in-final-of-tennis-s-fed-cup-after-wins.html
Russia and the  Czech Republic  will
meet in the final of women’s tennis’s Fed Cup after wins today
over defending champion  Italy  and  Belgium .  Vera Zvonareva defeated Italy’s Roberta Vinci 6-4, 6-2 to
secure Russia an unassailable 3-0 lead. Yesterday, Svetlana
Kuznetsova beat Vinci 6-2, 6-7 (4-7), 6-1 in Moscow and
Zvonareva had a  6-0, 6-2 victory over Sara Errani.  Anastasia Pavlyuchenkova made it 4-0 with a 7-6 (7-5), 7-6
(7-4) victory over Errani today, and Pavlyuchenkova and
Ekaterina Makarova defeated Alberta Brianti and Maria-Elena
Camerin in doubles for a 5-0 sweep.  The Czech Republic’s Iveta Benesova and Barbora Zahlavova
Strycova won the deciding doubles over Belgium’s Yanina
Wickmayer and Kirsten Flipkens today to give their nation a 3-2
victory in Charleroi.  Petra Kvitova beat Wickmayer 5-7, 6-4, 6-2 to put the
Czechs 2-1 ahead today, before Flipkens made it 2-2 by beating
Zahlavova Strycova 6-2, 6-3.  The U.S. a record 17-time Fed Cup champion, was demoted
from the top-division world group of women’s tennis’s most
prestigious team competition after a defeat by  Germany .  To contact the reporter on this story:
